#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:726
# f25b73854d0443a5aec74152d263ff0b
msgid "CSS embedded inside ``<style>`` tags is highlighted"
msgstr ""

#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:727
# 64b404ee72e84359a0817cd3af7a6f4c
msgid "Special characters that can be hard to distinguish such as non-breaking spaces, different types of hyphens, etc. are highlighted."
msgstr ""

#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:729
# 1ff32a2cfa794b979c194cb7beb36241
msgid "Links to other files in ``<a>`` tags, ``<img>`` and ``<link>`` tags all have the filenames highlighted. If the filename they point to does not exist, the filename is marked with a red underline."
msgstr ""

#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:734
# 631df3e113394663ad4cdb1ee749bdb9
msgid "Context sensitive help"
msgstr ""

#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:736
# 1c4c08cc0ce24566888f55e0edfe4f30
msgid "You can right click on an HTML tag name or a CSS property name to get help for that tag or property."
msgstr ""

#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:738
# 70d21aa7c99340d99f162391f9dd9adb
msgid "You can also hold down the Ctrl key and click on any filename inside a link tag to open that file in the editor automatically."
msgstr ""

#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:742
# 9086f039277e41a2b14b39f60337293a
msgid "Auto-complete"
msgstr ""

#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:744
# 429a3279656043a694f4a01b1ba71d5d
msgid "When editing an ebook, one of the most tedious tasks is creating links to other files inside the book, or to CSS stylesheets, or images. You have to figure out the correct filename and relative path to the file. The editor has auto-complete to make that easier."
msgstr ""

#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:749
# c4d1e0ba3aaa4f46b510fe96bfe698e2
msgid "As you type a filename, the editor automatically pops up suggestions. Simply use the Tab key to select the correct file name. The editor even offers suggestions for links pointing to an anchor inside another HTML file. After you type the ``#`` character, the editor will show you a list of all anchors in the target file, with a small snippet of text to help you choose the right anchor."
msgstr ""

#: ../../home/kovid/work/calibre/manual/edit.rst:755
# cd3439514f054cca970798f861ac0088
msgid "Note that unlike most other completion systems, the editor's completion system uses subsequence matching. This means that you can type just two or three letters from anywhere in the filename to complete the filename. For example, say you want the filename ``../images/arrow1.png``, you can simply type ``ia1`` and press Tab to complete the filename. When searching for matches, the completion system prioritizes letters that are at the start of a word, or immediately after a path separator. Once you get used to this system, you will find it saves you a lot of time and effort."
msgstr ""

